<page_title>Virtual experiments on springs</page_title>
<bg_image>sidebar1b.gif</bg_image>
<text> 

Springs are classic examples for learning Newtonian mechanics. Here are a collection of virtual experiments on spring systems.

   Conservation of angular momentum shown by two masses connected by a spring
   A spring and a mass
   Two springs and a mass
   A mass hung on a spring
   A mass hung on two springs
   Free fall of two masses linked by a spring
   Collision between a free mass and a mass connected to a spring



